metadata.name: Miniscapes #356
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #414
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

metadata.name: Sano #57
metadata.description:
Using Coronado’s algorithm as a starting point, Sano extends and embraces the notion of beauty existing in imperfection but allows for more impressionistic compositions with less structure, letting something atmospheric and understated emerge with subtle interactions that combine into dissonant chordal expressions infusing a breadth of emotion while maintaining a characteristic timbre.

Just as Coronado referenced a beat-up vintage guitar that had a patina and sound all its own, Sano refers to the vintage amp it was plugged into. A tube-amp from the 1960s with a spring reverb that when combined with single coils and hollow body of the guitar delivered screaming feedback as well as wonderfully gritty warm tones, which this algorithm attempts to echo visually.

There are 100 artist curated outputs in this short-form collection.

Keys:
S : save at current resolution
1 → 6 : save 2000x2500 → 12000x15000
(Chrome recommended for higher resolutions)

metadata.name: Hashed Cities #66
metadata.description:
This token generates a deterministic set of minimal, abstract buildings of varying widths, heights, transparencies, and patterns, assembling a skyline view of your own unique imaginary city. Each city comes with its own randomized city day.

Each mint has a native setting (Day or Night) which combined with the current time of viewing influences real-time movements of celestial bodies in your mint, e.g. on a mint with the Day setting, the sun will only appear when viewed during the day. The piece will re-render every minute.

The individual strokes of this token feature some of my latest developments of an algorithm that generatively simulates the texture of print imperfections. They are randomized at each render to give it a unique character. Note that depending on the complexity of each mint, some renders may introduce a brief pause. The aesthetics are greatly inspired by plotter art of early computer artists such as 'City Painting' by Grace C. Hertlein.

Made in p5js
Created Nov 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: {Lumina} #662
metadata.description:
The restitution of a breath
Your breath is your artwork

{Lumina} is part of the installation Σ Lumina taking place at Musée d’Orsay. A free live minting is scheduled from February 13th to March 10th, 2024. 

Breath, the vital essence, embodies our interconnection. It carries our shared heritage. A medium that helps Σ Lumina to unite the physical and the digital, the living with the coded. The voices of Orsay resonate within us, their breath becoming ours, landscaping our common creation.


Art curators of {Le Code d’Orsay}:
Christophe Leribault,
Président de l’Établissement public du musée d’Orsay et du musée de l’Orangerie
Virginie Donzeaud, Administratrice générale adjointe

16x16
HTML, js, Webgl
Location: Musée d’Orsay

metadata.name: Pigments #143
metadata.description:
“Pigments” is a generative art project that explores the beauty of optical color blending and the power of noise. 

At the heart of this work is a random composition of rectangles that are made up of dots. These pigments are arranged in multiple layers, each layer using a different color from one of the carefully curated color palettes. Each palette consists of three to five colors. 

As the pigments are shifted by random noise, new hues and patterns emerge, creating a lovely display of color and movement.

In live mode:
- Press [1]-[5] to change the resolution.
- Press [s] to save a png file at the current resolution.

This is my first generative art project. Created with p5js.

________

Looks best on high-resolution screens and viewed in live mode. When displayed on a low-resolution screen, an unintended moiré pattern may appear.
